Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.28,0:00:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to this month’s edition \Nof JW Broadcasting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.82,0:00:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are just a few highlights \Nthat we have in store for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.99,0:00:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you feel that you’ve missed \Npast opportunities
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.63,0:00:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to do more for Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.66,0:00:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Or do you feel that your age \Nor present circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.73,0:00:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,keep you from reaching out?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.97,0:00:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll see how one couple learned
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.97,0:00:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that there may be doors of activity available
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.57,0:00:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to those with a willing spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.24,0:00:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever received an assignment \Nthat you felt was overwhelming?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.05,0:00:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother and Sister Halme, \Nserving in West Africa,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.12,0:00:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,will share what helped them \Naccept such an assignment
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.12,0:00:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and remain spiritually strong \Nthrough difficult times.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.93,0:00:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you’re a regular pioneer,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.23,0:00:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,what role do you have \Nin strengthening the congregation?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.53,0:00:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll find this dramatization \Nvery insightful.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.94,0:00:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Our focus is on our ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.44,0:00:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in this May 2018 edition \Nof JW Broadcasting!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.13,0:01:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,To set the stage \Nfor the experiences in our program,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.63,0:01:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d like to talk to you \Nfor a few minutes on the theme
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.67,0:01:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“Invigorate Your Ministry—How?”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.74,0:01:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You dear brothers and sisters are having
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.17,0:01:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,a regular share in the preaching work,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.18,0:01:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and just think of the results.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.51,0:01:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Each year,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.78,0:01:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,about two billion hours \Nare spent in the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.68,0:01:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions of Bible studies are conducted,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.59,0:01:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and those being baptized \Nnumber into the hundreds of thousands.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.96,0:01:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are a Kingdom publisher,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.26,0:01:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you have had a share \Nin those thrilling statistics.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.96,0:01:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But there’s a potential danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.10,0:01:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,With so much to do in our life
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.77,0:02:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,—not just in the ministry \Nbut also with secular work,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.74,0:02:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,family responsibilities, \Nfor some, even health issues—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.81,0:02:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we can get into a rut.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.55,0:02:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not always easy to detect at first,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.42,0:02:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because in this age of technology
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.75,0:02:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we always feel busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.59,0:02:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But what consumes our day?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.36,0:02:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch this one-minute video,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.69,0:02:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and try to detect what’s going on \Nin the life of one brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.70,0:02:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,His life is in a rut.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.90,0:02:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Try to figure out why.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.38,0:03:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you say \Nthat this brother’s life is in a rut?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.61,0:03:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he’s active all day
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.75,0:03:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,—he always has something to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.18,0:03:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But it’s as if his mind \Nhas been kidnapped by his devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.06,0:04:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever had \Nthe experience of reading an e-mail
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.96,0:04:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,while someone \Nis trying to tell you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.70,0:04:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be embarrassing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.70,0:04:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,when you realize \Nthat they’ve asked you a question,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.07,0:04:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and they’re waiting for an answer,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.07,0:04:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but you have no idea what they asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.24,0:04:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s embarrassing, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.24,0:04:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if the person \Nwho is trying to speak to you is Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.35,0:04:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though we aren’t doing anything wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.85,0:04:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,our daily routine \Ncan occupy our attention so much
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.29,0:04:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are not able to hear \Nthe refreshing words of Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.72,0:04:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That can happen to any one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.23,0:04:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Even our spiritual activity \Ncan get into a rut.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.33,0:04:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,One Christian sister described it this way:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.67,0:04:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“I would go out in service,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.87,0:04:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“go to meetings, study, pray
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.34,0:04:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“—but I did it all on automatic control,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.38,0:04:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,never feeling anything.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.91,0:04:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever felt that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.38,0:05:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you see \Nall the happy servants of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.09,0:05:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,whose experiences \Nappear on JW Broadcasting,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.56,0:05:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and you say to yourself:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.56,0:05:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Why can’t I find that joy?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.69,0:05:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is my ministry in a rut?’
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.56,0:05:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you feel \Nlike a remote-control train
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.57,0:05:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that goes around and around on a track,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.33,0:05:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,working the same territory, \Nwith the same partner,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.11,0:05:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,saying the same thing at each door.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.77,0:05:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, there’s nothing wrong \Nwith being in a good routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.95,0:05:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But being in a rut can sap our energy
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.92,0:05:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and take the joy out of our service.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.75,0:05:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We could even come to view \Nour ministry as boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.02,0:05:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we feel invigorated \Nwhen we get good results:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.53,0:05:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We meet an interested person \Nwhen going from door to door
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.23,0:05:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,—we’re invigorated!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.07,0:05:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,An inactive person approaches the cart
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.47,0:05:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and wants to get in touch \Nwith the local congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.90,0:05:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,—we’re even more invigorated!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.91,0:05:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We start a Bible study \N—we’re on top of the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.54,0:06:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure you’ll agree,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.54,0:06:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,all those outcomes \Nare good reasons for joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.28,0:06:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is \Nthat we’re not always in control
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.82,0:06:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of getting those outcomes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.89,0:06:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In real life, \Nwe may spend an entire morning
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.22,0:06:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in the door-to-door work \Nwithout meeting an interested person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.69,0:06:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We may spend months
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.70,0:06:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,making return visits \Nwithout starting a study.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.07,0:06:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And once again, \Nour ministry can get into a rut.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.80,0:06:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, don’t misunderstand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.81,0:06:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not that we’re doing anything wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.28,0:06:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but we’re not getting \Nthe full joy out of doing what’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.88,0:06:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, Satan would love it
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.08,0:06:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,if our service to Jehovah \Nwere to fall into a rut.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.42,0:06:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He would love it if we lost our joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.82,0:06:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If we lose our joy, we lose hope,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.33,0:06:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we lose strength,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.33,0:06:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and we might even begin \Nto feel like giving up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.33,0:06:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The point is this, brothers and sisters:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.90,0:07:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If you feel that your ministry \Nhas fallen into a rut,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.11,0:07:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t be discouraged and don’t give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.21,0:07:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There are ways \Nthat we can invigorate our ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.54,0:07:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and serve Jehovah with renewed joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.41,0:07:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,To illustrate that:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.18,0:07:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you’ve had
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.75,0:07:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the frustrating experience \Nof locking yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.49,0:07:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,out of your house or apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.09,0:07:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, with a key, \Nopening the door is simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.89,0:07:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,A locked door \Nmight seem like an obstacle,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.33,0:07:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but it isn’t if you have the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.90,0:07:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And the same is true \Nwith invigorating our ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.97,0:07:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If we’ve fallen into a rut
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.21,0:07:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and if we’ve lost \Nthat feeling of joy in our service,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.18,0:07:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,there are a number of keys \Nthat can help us unlock the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.08,0:07:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look at one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.35,0:07:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Open your Bible \Nto 1 Corinthians 16:8, 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.86,0:07:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in these verses,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.32,0:07:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the apostle Paul was presented \Nwith a key of opportunity,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.46,0:08:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and he used it to open a door.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.50,0:08:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,First Corinthians 16:8, 9 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.64,0:08:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“But I am remaining in Ephesus
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.31,0:08:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“until the Festival of Pentecost,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.87,0:08:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“because a large door that leads to activity
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.65,0:08:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,has been opened to me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.48,0:08:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, the apostle Paul found a key,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.48,0:08:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and it didn’t require \Nmoving to another location.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.85,0:08:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, \Nthe key was to stay where he was
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.86,0:08:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and to take full advantage \Nof an opportunity right before him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.86,0:08:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, the key \Nto getting out of a rut in our ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.33,0:08:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is to take advantage of opportunities \Nwe have right where we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.04,0:08:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \Nhave you considered auxiliary pioneering
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.34,0:08:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,or regular pioneering?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.61,0:08:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What about learning a foreign language
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.78,0:08:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with the goal of helping \Na nearby group or congregation?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.32,0:09:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Opening one door often leads \Nto other doors of opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.12,0:09:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \Na brother named Jacob wrote this:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.76,0:09:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“When I was seven, \Nmany of my classmates were Vietnamese.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.23,0:09:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“I wanted to tell them about Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.64,0:09:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“so after a while \NI made plans to learn their language.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.01,0:09:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“For the most part,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.07,0:09:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“I learned by comparing \Nthe English and Vietnamese editions
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.18,0:09:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“of The Watchtower.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.05,0:09:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“I also made friends in a nearby \NVietnamese-language congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.52,0:09:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“When I was 18, I started pioneering.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.89,0:09:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“Later, I attended \Nthe Bible School for Single Brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.06,0:09:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“This helped me \Nwith my present pioneer assignment,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.79,0:09:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“where I am the only elder \Nin a Vietnamese-language group.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.00,0:09:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“Many Vietnamese people are amazed \Nthat I have learned their language.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.50,0:09:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“They invite me in, \Nand often I can study the Bible with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.91,0:09:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Some have progressed to baptism.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.28,0:09:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The point is, \Nour ministry is what we make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.32,0:10:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If we allow ourselves to remain in a rut,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.98,0:10:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,it will be boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.99,0:10:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If we use our keys \Nand if we take advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.86,0:10:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of opportunities that present themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.49,0:10:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we will invigorate our ministry \Nand give it new meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.90,0:10:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This doesn’t always involve \Nputting in more time in the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.30,0:10:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It could mean that we \Nsimply ‘make the best use of our time’
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.10,0:10:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,as Ephesians 5:16 says.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.11,0:10:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, there’s a saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.58,0:10:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“Don’t work harder; work smarter.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.25,0:10:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The key to working smarter
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.35,0:10:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,could be as simple \Nas switching things up a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.12,0:10:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,For example:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.12,0:10:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Could we work with different publishers \Ninstead of the same one all the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.79,0:10:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Could we try a different approach \Nto our presentation,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.73,0:10:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps making better use \Nof the Bible or our videos?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.93,0:10:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Could we engage \Nin other aspects of the ministry,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.90,0:10:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,such as cart witnessing \Nor phone witnessing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.87,0:11:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Could we use our time \Nmore effectively to reach people
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.08,0:11:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,when they’re most likely to be home?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.35,0:11:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s something else \Nwe could do to unlock a door
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.28,0:11:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and invigorate our ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.59,0:11:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Open your Bible to Acts 16:9, 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.33,0:11:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here the apostle Paul found
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.33,0:11:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,a unique way to unlock \Na door to greater joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.10,0:11:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Acts 16:9, 10 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.20,0:11:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“And during the night \Na vision appeared to Paul
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.21,0:11:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“—a Macedonian man \Nwas standing there urging him and saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.61,0:11:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Step over into Macedonia and help us.’
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.51,0:11:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“As soon as he had seen the vision,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.95,0:11:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“we tried to go into Macedonia,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.49,0:11:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“drawing the conclusion \Nthat God had summoned us
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.69,0:11:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to declare the good news to them.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.06,0:11:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice, Paul didn’t think of all the reasons
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.06,0:11:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,he couldn’t step into Macedonia.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.57,0:11:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No, he took action
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.57,0:12:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,as soon as he was presented \Nwith the opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.80,0:12:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul unlocked the door \Nto invigorate his ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.81,0:12:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes we think \Nthat only those who are young
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.75,0:12:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,can reach out to pioneer \Nor to serve where the need is greater.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.75,0:12:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But that’s not always the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.25,0:12:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You parents may be able to unlock \Na door of opportunity for yourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.29,0:12:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and think of the example \Nyou set for your children when you do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.30,0:12:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what a mother named Tara discovered:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.30,0:12:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“I started pioneering \Nwhen my youngest daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.54,0:12:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,was in elementary school,” she says.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.34,0:12:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“It was important to me
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.41,0:12:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“that my children see me serving Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.78,0:12:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to the best of my ability \Nas I encouraged them to reach out.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.22,0:12:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Tara’s husband, Anthony,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.22,0:12:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,saw the effect \Nthat his wife’s pioneering had
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.92,0:12:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and, in time, \Nhe too joined the ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.03,0:13:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what he said:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.26,0:13:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“When Tara became a pioneer,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.26,0:13:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“it made an immediate impact
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.53,0:13:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“on daughters number one and number two,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.47,0:13:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“and they became pioneers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.87,0:13:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“When I became a pioneer,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.87,0:13:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“daughters number three \Nand number four followed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.84,0:13:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“I wish I had pursued \Nfull-time service sooner,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.71,0:13:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,as it made a huge impact \Non the spirituality of the family.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.55,0:13:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I can relate to this experience
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.82,0:13:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the good example of my parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.23,0:13:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother was baptized in Canada
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.93,0:13:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in 1940 when she was 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.37,0:13:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s Witnesses \Nhad just been banned in Canada.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.27,0:13:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Her father had already died,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.51,0:13:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and her mother was opposed at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.51,0:13:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers had very little money,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.04,0:13:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but they encouraged \Nmy mother to pursue spiritual goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.88,0:13:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,With that encouragement,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.88,0:13:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,she started pioneering in 1942
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.79,0:14:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,while the ban was still on in Canada.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.19,0:14:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1947, she was invited \Nto become a special pioneer
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.69,0:14:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in the province of Quebec.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.03,0:14:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, \Nspecial pioneers were required
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.23,0:14:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to spend 200 hours \Neach month in the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.54,0:14:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,With basically no money \Nand no family support,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.51,0:14:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,she accepted that assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.78,0:14:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This picture was taken \Nwhen she and her pioneer partner
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.41,0:14:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,were boarding the train to Quebec.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.28,0:14:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever I see this picture,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.55,0:14:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it reminds me \Nof the intrepid spirit that my mother had
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.46,0:14:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,—not being afraid \Nto take on a challenging assignment,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.33,0:14:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but putting complete trust in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.13,0:14:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That spirit encourages me even to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.27,0:14:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,My father has that same spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.90,0:14:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In the summer of 1976, \Nwhen I was 11 years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.21,0:14:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,a new arrangement was announced \Nat our district convention
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.28,0:14:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,—auxiliary pioneering.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.51,0:15:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You could be an auxiliary pioneer
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.95,0:15:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,if you could devote 60 hours \Nin one month to the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.12,0:15:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The month of October 1976 \Nhad five weekends.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.73,0:15:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My father encouraged \Nour whole congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.00,0:15:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to try auxiliary pioneering that month.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.70,0:15:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So many brothers and sisters, including me,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.13,0:15:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,decided to get a taste of pioneering.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.17,0:15:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a wonderful experience
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.74,0:15:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that I will never forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.34,0:15:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Parents, your good example \Nwill help your children
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.75,0:15:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to have a living ministry \Nof their own that they will love.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.79,0:15:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers and sisters, \Nif you find yourself in a rut,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.56,0:15:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no reason to stay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.89,0:15:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve discussed several ways \Nto reinvigorate our ministry,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.06,0:15:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and with Jehovah’s help \Nwe will be successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.64,0:15:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s meet a few brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.40,0:15:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,who’ve expanded \Nand invigorated their ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.54,0:16:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re sure you’ll appreciate their stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.78,0:16:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Our first experience comes from Brazil,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.85,0:16:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in South America.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.88,0:16:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Cristiano and Joana Souza
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.65,0:16:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,found the key to invigorating their ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.79,0:16:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in a congregation letter \Nencouraging individuals
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.26,0:16:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to apply for the School \Nfor Kingdom Evangelizers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.23,0:16:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What new blessings \Ndid they experience by reaching out?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.88,0:16:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We had our own house,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.88,0:16:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain amount of comfort.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.15,0:16:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband had a stable job,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.21,0:16:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was doing a lot where we were.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.32,0:16:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I had Bible studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.09,0:16:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I was already a regular pioneer,\Nso I thought I was doing enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.99,0:16:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It was fine to stay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.76,0:16:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We’d often see the younger ones
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.76,0:16:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,going to Bethel,\Ngoing to serve as special pioneers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.20,0:17:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And once we reached our 40’s,\NI thought that since we’re getting older,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.34,0:17:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we won’t be able to reach out\Nand do more for Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.31,0:17:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But after a letter\Nwas read to the congregations,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.01,0:17:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,well, that was really \Nthe starting point for us to see
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.14,0:17:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that we could do more for Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.35,0:17:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,When I heard that there was\Na school for couples up to 65 years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.65,0:17:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, “Cristiano, it’s now or never.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.02,0:17:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So immediately at the first convention\Nthat held a meeting for interested couples,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.49,0:17:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,we attended the meeting\Nand realized that out of the requirements
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.26,0:17:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there was one\Nthat my husband didn’t meet yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.00,0:17:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,which was two years as a regular pioneer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.37,0:17:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought, ‘Why not?’
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.11,0:17:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,After the convention,\NI applied to be a regular pioneer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.41,0:17:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So we made plans to attend the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.91,0:17:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But we didn’t want to stay there\Nwaiting to be accepted,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.01,0:17:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,as there were no guarantees of being accepted
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.02,0:17:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in the same year in which we applied.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.02,0:17:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We sold our house.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.02,0:17:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And two weeks later,\Nwe had sold all the furniture.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.56,0:17:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So we made arrangements\Nto serve where the need was greater.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.53,0:18:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We took only what was necessary in our car.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.57,0:18:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But “what is necessary” is always too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.30,0:18:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get to the territory, you realize\Nyou didn’t even need everything you took.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.07,0:18:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We were really excited because we knew \Nthe brothers were expecting us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.08,0:18:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a gas station\Nthat belonged to a brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.55,0:18:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and when we arrived,\Nthe whole congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.95,0:18:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,was waiting for us there \Nto welcome us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.05,0:18:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Nine people!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.25,0:18:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And that had a great impact on us,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.95,0:18:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,because you could see \Nthe expression on their faces;
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.39,0:18:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it was as if they were asking for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.06,0:18:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They helped us a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.26,0:18:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I can honestly say \Nthat they helped us more
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.27,0:18:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,than we helped them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.11,0:18:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now they would be able\Nto have regular meetings
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.51,0:18:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,—a public talk every week.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.51,0:18:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, we were in São Paulo\Nand we had all the meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.35,0:18:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But in these remote areas, they need\Nspiritual food from Jehovah so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.82,0:18:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But there needs to be people \Nwilling to go and help.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.96,0:19:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Then one day,\Nwe had a wonderful surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.33,0:19:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,A brother called me and said,\N“Cristiano, have you checked your e-mails?”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.83,0:19:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We’d received a letter\Ninviting us to the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.54,0:19:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The school really is a gift from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.21,0:19:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve encouraged others that I know\Nto attend the school
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.68,0:19:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because you really feel\Nhow Jehovah cares for his organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.58,0:19:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And a small thing we can do\Nis simply give our best,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.79,0:19:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and the school helps us do just that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.32,0:19:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,—find out what is our best.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.19,0:19:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We were assigned\Nto a congregation called Itiruçu.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.66,0:19:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers are very loving,\Nand we’re really happy in our assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.50,0:19:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I do miss my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.37,0:19:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s nice to have your own house
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.37,0:19:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and not to have to worry about paying rent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.64,0:19:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I miss my hairdresser.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.61,0:20:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But nothing compares\Nto the blessings and the joy
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.28,0:20:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes from serving \Nwhere there’s a need.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.92,0:20:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This joy helps us to combat \Nany homesickness we feel
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.79,0:20:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and stops us from developing\Nany desire to go back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.69,0:20:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In the big city,\Neverything’s very rushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.23,0:20:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I would only see my wife\Nwhen I got home from work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.40,0:20:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d be tired, and then also\Nhave to care for congregational matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.57,0:20:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So there wasn’t much time\Nfor us to be together.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.34,0:20:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it’s completely different.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.34,0:20:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We have much more time\N—during the ministry,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.01,0:20:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in the congregation, \Nbeing together at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.35,0:20:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So for us as a family,\Nit has been very positive, very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.22,0:20:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re not tired.\NWe’re not old in the sense—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.25,0:20:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No we’re not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.25,0:20:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,—of saying that we’ve got no more to give.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.29,0:20:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We really believe we can do more for Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.89,0:20:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And we want to do more for Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.93,0:20:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The school is proof\Nthat he wants us to do more.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.77,0:20:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to use our life to the full\Nto serve Jehovah wherever he sends us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.87,0:20:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We are willing to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.87,0:20:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We feel it’s the only way\Nto say a big “thank you”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.57,0:21:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jehovah\Nfor everything he’s done for us
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.95,0:21:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,—the territory, school, \Nthe brothers, and Bible students.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.95,0:21:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What better way to thank Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.10,0:21:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you feel the way \Nthat Brother and Sister Souza felt
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.73,0:21:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,—that you’ve missed the chance \Nto do more for Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.47,0:21:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They learned there were \Ndoors of opportunity accessible to them
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.24,0:21:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,if they were willing to reach out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.51,0:21:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Their choice to make themselves available
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.91,0:21:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,resulted in rich blessings.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.55,0:21:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But did you notice \Nwhen those blessings started?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.45,0:21:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Before the school,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.45,0:21:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,they chose to serve \Nwhere the need was greater.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.09,0:21:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This had a profound effect on them,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.76,0:21:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,deepening their appreciation \Nfor spiritual provisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.10,0:21:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If you desire to enliven your ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.47,0:22:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,by means of theocratic education,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.37,0:22:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,consider ways you can prepare \Nyour heart before you attend.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.21,0:22:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The Souzas’ example proves
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.68,0:22:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that even the road \Nto expanding our ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.98,0:22:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,can be deeply satisfying.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.78,0:22:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,When we’re faced \Nwith challenging assignments,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.05,0:22:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,reliance on Jehovah is of utmost importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.62,0:22:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In what ways can we show that reliance?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.33,0:22:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I have the pleasure of introducing you \Nto a friend of mine,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.93,0:22:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Shane Brady, who is presently serving \Nalong with his wife, Iolanda,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.34,0:22:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,at the branch in Finland.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.51,0:22:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Shane Brady and I \Npreviously worked together
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.17,0:22:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,at the Canada branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.04,0:22:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Shane has been involved \Nin legally defending our brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.55,0:22:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,for the past 22 years in many countries,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.25,0:22:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,including Armenia, Kazakhstan, \Nand Kyrgyzstan.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.76,0:22:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Shane, it’s good to see you. \NHow are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.09,0:22:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m doing very well. \NIt’s great to see you too, Mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.66,0:23:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Shane, we want to ask you,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.26,0:23:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What have been some of the challenges
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.43,0:23:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that you’ve faced \Nin accepting these assignments
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.10,0:23:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in various countries in the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.24,0:23:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there certainly have been \Na few challenges.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.61,0:23:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,One is frequent travel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.71,0:23:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Another is language;
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.71,0:23:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,each country that we assist \Nhas its own language.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.91,0:23:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Some court cases are very stressful,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.25,0:23:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and at times, we’ve faced firsthand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.19,0:23:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the hatred of our opposers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.19,0:23:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. And you know, Shane, \Nin spite of all that,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.73,0:23:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you and your wife have always been willing \Nto go on these assignments.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.26,0:23:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We appreciate your spirit so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.77,0:23:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there an experience \Nthat you can share with us
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.44,0:23:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that would give us a taste \Nof the kinds of situations
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.44,0:23:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that you’ve had to deal with \Nin these countries?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.64,0:23:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there have been many experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.91,0:23:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But one experience comes to mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.91,0:23:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A few months ago, \Nthere was a special pioneer,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.05,0:23:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and a case was started against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.05,0:24:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And if the decision was negative, \Nit could have had very serious consequences
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.12,0:24:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,for our work in that country.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.12,0:24:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So we did our best \Nto present a strong defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.49,0:24:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But as the trial progressed,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.36,0:24:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,things didn’t seem to be going so well.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.50,0:24:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But on the last day of the trial, \Neverything changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.10,0:24:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We presented a motion,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.27,0:24:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and we asked the judge \Nto terminate the case against the brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.61,0:24:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Personally, I didn’t think \Nit would actually work.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.28,0:24:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But one older brother who we’ve worked with
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.51,0:24:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,over the years always told us,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.15,0:24:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“We need to give Jehovah something to bless.”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.42,0:24:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we did, and the results \Nwere quite unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.42,0:24:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,When we made the motion, the judge turned \Nto the prosecutor and asked,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.69,0:24:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, what’s your opinion?”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.43,0:24:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And to our surprise, \Nthe prosecutor agreed with our request,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.86,0:24:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and he even went beyond what we asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.93,0:24:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He said to the judge \Nthat the government official
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.74,0:24:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that started the case \Nagainst our brother should be punished.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.94,0:24:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the judge agreed; \Nthe case was terminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.74,0:24:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,When we were walking out of the courtroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.14,0:24:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked at the other brothers with me \Nand we all said the same thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.01,0:25:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“What happened?”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.78,0:25:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It was obvious\N—Jehovah had intervened.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.19,0:25:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s wonderful, Shane.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.55,0:25:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish we had more time \Nto hear many more experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.12,0:25:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But could you just share \Nat least one more with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.69,0:25:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.46,0:25:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In another land where our work \Nis not recognized,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.57,0:25:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,on the night of the Memorial,\Na number of the brothers were arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.90,0:25:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,for so-called illegal religious activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.14,0:25:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They were all convicted at trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.14,0:25:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So arrangements were made \Nto appeal each of those cases,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.38,0:25:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were heard \Nbefore a different appeal court judge.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.98,0:25:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What at first seemed quite negative, \Nthe loss at trial,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.32,0:25:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,turned out to be an amazing result.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.75,0:25:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me give you just one example.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.02,0:25:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In one of the appeals, \Nas we were presenting the appeal,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.09,0:25:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,not long into the case, \Nthe appeal court judge stopped us,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.13,0:25:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and he began to ask us \Nmany questions about the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.17,0:25:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and about what Jehovah’s Witnesses believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.27,0:25:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So for quite some time, \Nwe answered these Biblical questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.67,0:25:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the case continued.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.67,0:26:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And then after some minutes, \Nthe judge stopped us again.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.74,0:26:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And this time the judge said, \N“I remember reading in the Bible”—
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.21,0:26:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The judge said this, \N“I remember reading in the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.28,0:26:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“that Jesus said: \N‘If they have persecuted me,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.65,0:26:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,they will persecute you also.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.79,0:26:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So we said to the judge: \N“Yes, indeed. Jesus said that.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.56,0:26:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The judge asked, \N“Do you think that’s the reason why
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.96,0:26:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s Witnesses \Nare having problems in this region?”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.20,0:26:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what could we say \Nbut agree with the judge.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.84,0:26:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But that wasn’t the end of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.27,0:26:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,As the case continued a few minutes more, \Nthe judge stopped us again.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.51,0:26:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And this time the judge said: \N“You know, I’m not sure if Jesus said this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.31,0:26:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“It’s in the Bible where he said:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.95,0:26:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Where there are two or three \Ngathered together,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.62,0:26:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,there I am in your midst.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.62,0:26:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And we assured the judge, \N“Indeed, those are Jesus’ words.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.52,0:26:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The judge looked out at this old courtroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.03,0:26:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,which was filled \Nwith our brothers and sisters, and he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.83,0:26:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, Jesus must be in our midst today.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.70,0:27:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We felt like breaking into applause.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.17,0:27:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of the court hearing,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.17,0:27:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the judge ruled in our favor \Nand acquitted the brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.51,0:27:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and the judges in all of the other cases \Nalso acquitted our brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.38,0:27:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just a thrilling experience!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.65,0:27:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that’s wonderful; \Nthat’s wonderful, Shane.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.88,0:27:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much \Nfor sharing those experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.15,0:27:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, despite the challenges \Nthat you’ve had to face,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.72,0:27:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you feel about the way \Nyou and Iolanda have benefited
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.52,0:27:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,from being involved in accepting \Nthese challenging assignments
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.53,0:27:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in various parts of the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.53,0:27:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we have benefited \Nin so many ways, Mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.43,0:27:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Our relationship with Jehovah has deepened.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.84,0:27:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, our trust in Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.84,0:27:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,has been strengthened.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.07,0:27:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ve experienced firsthand the love
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.94,0:27:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of the amazing worldwide brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.71,0:27:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Could I just share one experience about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.78,0:27:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.78,0:27:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Two years ago, we were involved in a case
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.25,0:27:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,where police had raided \Na congregation meeting in one country.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.82,0:27:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They had brutally beaten the brothers \Nand threatened the sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.06,0:28:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.06,0:28:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Some weeks later in the court case
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.36,0:28:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that started against the brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.93,0:28:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,(that the police brought \Nagainst the brothers),
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.43,0:28:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,during that court case, \Nthe police repeatedly tried
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.44,0:28:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to arrest me and another brother \NI was working with.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.81,0:28:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Over two days they were trying to arrest us.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.51,0:28:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in the courthouse, \Nthey tried to detain and arrest us.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.05,0:28:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And all through this, my wife, Iolanda, \Nwas watching what was happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.68,0:28:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But do you know what was so remarkable?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.05,0:28:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It was that despite the brutal treatment
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.69,0:28:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers and sisters \Nhad endured just a few weeks earlier
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.46,0:28:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,at the hands \Nof these very same police officers,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.03,0:28:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,those dear brothers and sisters \Ncame to our aid.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.60,0:28:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They were like a wall \Nof protection around us,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.63,0:28:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and they would not leave our side \Nuntil the ordeal was done.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.61,0:28:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It was love in action.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.01,0:28:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So to answer your question, \Nwe have benefited in so many ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.28,0:28:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t regret for a moment \Naccepting this thrilling assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.28,0:28:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you so much, Shane.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.05,0:28:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Please give our love to Iolanda as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.49,0:29:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We appreciate the tremendous work \Nthat you’re accomplishing,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.52,0:29:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and may Jehovah’s spirit \Ncontinue to be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.29,0:29:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s our privilege.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.29,0:29:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We look forward to continuing \Nto work with you, Mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.50,0:29:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, \Nwhat if getting yourself out of a rut
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.50,0:29:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,takes longer than expected?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.17,0:29:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re going to meet a couple from Italy
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.41,0:29:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,who had the goal to participate \Nin a special preaching campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.74,0:29:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,These campaigns \Ncan be a life-changing experience
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.55,0:29:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,for the publishers involved,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.55,0:29:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,pushing them, sometimes, \Nfar out of their comfort zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.25,0:29:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the Di Giacintos \Nfaced trying circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.59,0:29:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that prevented them from participating,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.19,0:29:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but they did not stop knocking \Non this door of opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.70,0:29:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We live in a beautiful, \Nquiet town in central Italy,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.51,0:29:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,between the sea and the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.07,0:29:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We have many friends, \Nsome of whom are good cooks.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.81,0:30:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We have been serving for some years \Nin a Romanian-language congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.95,0:30:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and we preach to people who have moved \Nto Italy to seek a better life.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.69,0:30:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,When we heard the announcement \Nabout the special campaign,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.76,0:30:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,we looked at each other \Nand said, “Let’s go!”
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.83,0:30:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,‘A large door of activity’ \Nwas opening up to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.47,0:30:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was a problem—my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.74,0:30:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I would need a month’s leave of absence,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.81,0:30:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and that would be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.88,0:30:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We prayed, and we did research.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.08,0:30:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And during family worship, \Nwe decided that in order to participate,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.45,0:30:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I would ask for a one-month leave from work.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.56,0:30:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah had something else in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.86,0:30:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that would create \Nthe right circumstances for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.67,0:30:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,When I arrived at work the next day, \NI found an unexpected situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.00,0:30:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the failing economy,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.00,0:30:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,my boss gave me and some other employees
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.04,0:31:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a letter of dismissal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.48,0:31:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I was not at all worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.48,0:31:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I trusted in Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.41,0:31:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and I knew that this new situation
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.88,0:31:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,would allow me \Nto participate in the campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.82,0:31:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Participating in this campaign \Nis a dream come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.19,0:31:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted to participate in 2013,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.63,0:31:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but unfortunately things in life \Ndo not always go as we would like.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.97,0:31:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We received some truly shocking news.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.91,0:31:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,My father had been diagnosed \Nwith pancreatic cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.25,0:31:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionally, it was not easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.65,0:31:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The tranquillity \Nwe had dreamed and hoped for
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.75,0:31:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,was almost gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.56,0:31:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing that could help me \Nat that moment was
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.86,0:31:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the hope for what Jehovah promises us.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.30,0:31:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to my father’s death,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.80,0:32:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I began to experience panic attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.50,0:32:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I was afraid of something that didn’t exist
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.08,0:32:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,—afraid of not being able to move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.01,0:32:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the kind of emotion \Nthat leaves a lump in your throat,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.28,0:32:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can’t even breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.99,0:32:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that only Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.22,0:32:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,could help me fill the void that I felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.96,0:32:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,After a family worship,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.63,0:32:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Fabio and I decided to turn in \Nour regular pioneer applications.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.33,0:32:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt Jehovah at my side,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.80,0:32:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,embracing and supporting me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.77,0:32:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, they turned out to be \Nthe three most beautiful years of our lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.98,0:32:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,which also allowed us \Nto participate in this beautiful campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.45,0:32:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,In Romania, there are \Nmany isolated territories
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.05,0:32:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that local brothers cannot work \Nbecause of the great distances to be covered.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.60,0:33:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It is really exciting to reach many people
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.03,0:33:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,by traveling on dirt roads \Nthat are often muddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.38,0:33:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The people are generous, \Nhospitable, and genuine.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.19,0:33:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They almost always invite us into their homes
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.66,0:33:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and are willing to talk to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.73,0:33:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Talking to people who do not know Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.40,0:33:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and who are still very much interested \Nin doctrinal topics is really exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.91,0:33:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Experiencing firsthand \Na culture different from ours,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.75,0:33:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing people who live a more simple life,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.55,0:34:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and trying to understand their needs
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.92,0:34:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is an experience that we will take with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.32,0:34:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And it will help us \Nto preach more effectively
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.56,0:34:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in our assigned \Ncongregation’s territory in Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.74,0:34:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we are stronger than when we left home.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.51,0:34:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This experience has made us \Nlove the ministry even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.62,0:34:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We look forward to returning \Nto our home territory with renewed zeal.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.79,0:34:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We are certain that Jehovah will guide us \Nto further service opportunities
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.53,0:34:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to help others know \Nhis wonderful purposes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.94,0:34:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What blessings did this couple experience
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.37,0:34:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,by staying focused on their goal?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.21,0:34:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It brought them the joy of full-time service.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.44,0:34:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even the threat of unemployment
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.68,0:35:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,caused them to waver \Nin their determination to participate.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.68,0:35:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,After the campaign, \Nthey returned to their home territory
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.52,0:35:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,with a renewed energy and zeal.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.02,0:35:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,When we stay focused on Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.79,0:35:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,even in the most trying of circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.76,0:35:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it will strengthen our resolve \Nto serve him faithfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.50,0:35:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Juuso and Pauliina Halme, \Na couple from Finland,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.34,0:35:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,now serving in Sierra Leone, \Nin West Africa,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.68,0:35:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,were invited to accept an assignment
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.28,0:35:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that seemed overwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.61,0:35:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened when some \Nof their worst fears came true?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.42,0:35:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Jehovah provide \N“the power beyond what is normal”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.26,0:35:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to help them to endure?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.79,0:35:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Worrying doesn’t help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.03,0:35:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no need, really, \Nto worry about what could happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.20,0:35:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it happens, let Jehovah show
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.24,0:35:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,how he can handle the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.84,0:36:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He can actually do it in ways \Nyou could never expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.78,0:36:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We are Juuso and Pauliina Halme.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.35,0:36:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We loved our assignment \Nin the Finland branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.35,0:36:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We had wonderful friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.28,0:36:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Our families, they were very close.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.52,0:36:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We had time to be with them often.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.39,0:36:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In 2014, we got the Yearbook
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.66,0:36:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and that had an account of Sierra Leone.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.06,0:36:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was reading that account,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.20,0:36:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and I remember saying \Na couple of times to Pauliina,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.74,0:36:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“This would be a tough place.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.87,0:36:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,After coming back from Gilead, \NI couldn’t believe it;
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.77,0:36:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we got a letter saying
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.48,0:36:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that we had been reassigned \Nto Sierra Leone branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.28,0:36:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was a huge change for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.28,0:36:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what we did \Nis we Googled Sierra Leone
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.55,0:36:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and what we saw was only about a civil war
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.62,0:36:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that took place years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.63,0:36:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,An Ebola outbreak \Nwas starting in West Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.90,0:36:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of our relatives \Nwere worried about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.63,0:37:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That was our impression, \Nfirst impression, about the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.50,0:37:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We were terrified, and we couldn’t sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.24,0:37:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We just prayed the whole night.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.24,0:37:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And really, with the reassignment, \Nour greatest fear was my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.91,0:37:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He had been terminally ill \Nfor about two years,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.15,0:37:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and we knew that at some point \Nit would get worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.62,0:37:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He would need more help \Nand also Juuso’s mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.39,0:37:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So were we able to travel back to Finland?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.49,0:37:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s so expensive, \Nand we didn’t have savings.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.80,0:37:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Although we had all those fears,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.07,0:37:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,after praying about it a lot,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.27,0:37:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we just realized \Nthat we could not say no.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.17,0:37:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And we realized \Nthat this assignment was from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.47,0:37:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.74,0:37:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s get to work. \NLet’s give our best to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.32,0:37:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Then actually in three months, \Nour greatest fear came true.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.25,0:37:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It really happened
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.26,0:37:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that Juuso’s mom \Ncalled us and she told us
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.56,0:38:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that Juuso’s father’s situation had changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.06,0:38:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So we immediately started to check flights.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.63,0:38:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the next call was
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.30,0:38:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that he had passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.81,0:38:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We were able to get flights, fly back home,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.21,0:38:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,support my mother, \Nand help with the funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.31,0:38:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We were so happy \Nwhen we finally got back to Sierra Leone.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.42,0:38:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we thought that we could focus
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.95,0:38:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,on our assignment and on our work at Bethel.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.16,0:38:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then one day, we got another \NSkype call from my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.86,0:38:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he told us \Nthat he was diagnosed
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.03,0:38:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,with an extremely aggressive cancer,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.80,0:38:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’s in hospital now, \Nand he asked us
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.20,0:38:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to come back to Finland for a visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.17,0:38:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We had a beautiful ten days \Ntogether with my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.41,0:38:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, finally, he passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.21,0:38:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that was really \Nthe lowest point in our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.62,0:38:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That came out of the blue; \Nwe were not expecting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.29,0:39:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We had two widows to take care of.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.16,0:39:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So we were really wondering
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.49,0:39:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,if we could continue \Nin our assignment in Sierra Leone.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.96,0:39:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, \None of our favorite scriptures was
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.53,0:39:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah 30:15
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.67,0:39:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that “your strength will be \Nin keeping calm and showing trust.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.34,0:39:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we poured our hearts \Nto Jehovah in prayer,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.64,0:39:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we could see so well how Jehovah \Nhelped us to stay calm
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.52,0:39:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and have peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.15,0:39:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And we got some good advice here \Nfrom mature brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.32,0:39:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,not to make any quick decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.79,0:39:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So we put our trust in Jehovah, \Nand we could just see
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.63,0:39:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was Jehovah’s will that we continue \Nin our assignment in Sierra Leone.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.23,0:39:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact is that, really, \Nthe blessings always
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.64,0:39:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,surpass any of the challenges.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.41,0:39:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have come to love \Nour assignment in Sierra Leone.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.61,0:39:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters, \Nthey are so faithful in Sierra Leone
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.98,0:40:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,despite their problems and challenges.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.95,0:40:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They give beautiful examples for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.75,0:40:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Being in a country where there is a lot \Nof potential, a lot of work, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.79,0:40:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . you can have as many Bible studies \Nas you can conduct,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.19,0:40:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so it’s just a preaching paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.26,0:40:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Going through these experiences,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.47,0:40:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,we are so happy that Jehovah \Nis the Writer of our story.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.74,0:40:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And, for sure, \Nthere’s a happy end.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.51,0:40:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If he wants to take you there, go there;
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.48,0:40:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,see what Jehovah \Nhas in mind for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.95,0:40:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you can really \N“taste and see that Jehovah is good.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.82,0:40:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite heartbreaking challenges,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.35,0:40:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the Halmes saw Jehovah’s loving support
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.59,0:40:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and they did not give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.36,0:40:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,When we extend ourselves for Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.33,0:40:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,we can be confident \Nthat he will help us in good times
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.43,0:40:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and in difficult times.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.64,0:40:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We learn that we are safe \Nwith Jehovah, come what may.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.74,0:41:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What quality do you need \Nto serve in a foreign land,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.81,0:41:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,like Brother and Sister Di Giacinto,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.28,0:41:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,or to face the fear of the unknown, \Nlike Brother and Sister Halme?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.22,0:41:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We need courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.99,0:41:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,As was announced last year,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.32,0:41:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,courage is \Nthis year’s regional convention theme.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.26,0:41:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The drama presentation \Nwill focus on a Bible character
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.27,0:41:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that needed great courage \Nto accomplish his ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.70,0:41:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s our pleasure \Nto present a preview of the drama
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.07,0:41:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The Story of Jonah \N—A Lesson in Courage and Mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.22,0:41:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Papa says you are a prophet.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.62,0:41:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a prophet.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.49,0:41:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to run away from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.76,0:41:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But when has Jehovah ever asked a prophet
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.90,0:41:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to go to a foreign land
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.00,0:42:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to preach judgment against it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.77,0:42:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the people?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.74,0:42:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They worship gods of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.31,0:42:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think they’re like?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.98,0:42:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what will you do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.89,0:42:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to go back inside, Joanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.92,0:42:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No! We can talk to Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.29,0:42:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Joanna!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.12,0:42:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t go to Nineveh.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.43,0:42:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can’t do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.66,0:42:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re Jehovah’s prophet.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.46,0:42:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.53,0:42:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Go home, Joanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.82,0:42:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,O Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.25,0:42:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the depths of the Grave,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.29,0:42:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I cry to you for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.73,0:43:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What will become of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.77,0:43:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt you eagerly anticipate \Nthis year’s regional convention program
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.61,0:43:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,held around the world starting this month.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.65,0:43:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of the segments on our program thus far
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.58,0:43:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,have featured some aspect \Nof preaching in a foreign land.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.59,0:43:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If current circumstances \Ndon’t permit you to serve in this capacity,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.86,0:43:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,be assured that there’s much you can do
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.36,0:43:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in your home territory \Nto revive your ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.00,0:43:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,For example—
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.67,0:43:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the over 100,000 publishers \Nin South Korea,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.04,0:43:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,there are more than \N40,000 zealous regular pioneers.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.84,0:43:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What efforts have they made
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.84,0:43:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach more people \Nin frequently worked territory?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.35,0:43:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.95,0:43:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I started pioneering \Nless than a year after I got baptized,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.59,0:44:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,so I was eager to sharpen
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.16,0:44:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,my preaching skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.62,0:44:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I really wanted to share my hope with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.39,0:44:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But it’s so hard to meet people
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.23,0:44:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,at their homes during the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.90,0:44:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if we do meet them,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.73,0:44:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s not easy to start a conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.13,0:44:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Our congregation organized \Nconvenience store witnessing
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.84,0:44:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,from 7:00 a.m. to 9:00 a.m.,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.34,0:44:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so I thought this might be \Na good way to reach people
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.24,0:44:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and have meaningful conversations.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.81,0:44:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But the thing is that I’m not \Na morning person,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.92,0:44:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,so getting up early was not easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.25,0:44:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So I had to make some adjustments.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.99,0:44:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried not to make plans
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.66,0:44:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or to stay up late the night before.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.26,0:44:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The sample presentations \Nfrom our meetings were also very helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.00,0:44:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In the past, I hardly got the chance \Nto open the Bible while I was preaching,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.27,0:44:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but now I have a few Bible studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.28,0:44:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the time we spend traveling \Nfrom one convenience store to the next
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.75,0:45:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is very uplifting spiritually \Nbecause we use that time
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.55,0:45:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to share our preaching skills \Nand build each other up.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.59,0:45:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Having a regular share \Nin convenience store witnessing
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.56,0:45:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,has allowed me to be \Nmore productive in the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.09,0:45:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like I’m progressing spiritually
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.63,0:45:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and becoming a better minister \Nof the good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.80,0:45:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,On weekdays, I work to support my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.64,0:45:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So I would usually go out in field service
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.11,0:45:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,on the weekends.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.27,0:45:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But it wasn’t easy \Nto find people at their homes
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.18,0:45:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,because they usually make plans and go out.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.38,0:45:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.08,0:45:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s hard to get excited \Nabout the preaching work
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.62,0:45:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when you’re not meeting many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.05,0:45:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to set \Na good example for my family,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.36,0:45:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but I found it a real challenge \Nto maintain my zeal for the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.13,0:45:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So I began to regularly participate \Nin evening witnessing
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.83,0:45:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,on Mondays, Tuesdays, and Fridays.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.24,0:46:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I usually get off work around 5:00 p.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.47,0:46:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,After a long day at work,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.84,0:46:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s not always easy to get dressed
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.78,0:46:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to go out in the field ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.78,0:46:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But I kept up with my return visits
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.55,0:46:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and had some really encouraging experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.29,0:46:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,A young man I had been visiting
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.26,0:46:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,accepted a Bible study, \Nand he’s making fine progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.76,0:46:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My children are able to see \Nhow much joy I get from the ministry,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.00,0:46:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and so now they too \Nare able to give a bold witness
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.47,0:46:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in their own words, \Neven in the face of opposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.51,0:46:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I am very proud of my children.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.17,0:46:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Training and teaching them how to make
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.54,0:46:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,effective return visits and Bible studies
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.01,0:46:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,brings me great joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.72,0:46:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We serve in a small rural town
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.12,0:46:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,where many leave home \Nearly in the morning to work in the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.95,0:46:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and they return late at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.96,0:46:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s not easy
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.36,0:46:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to find people at home during the daytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.73,0:46:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if we do find them at their doors,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.13,0:46:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s not easy to develop \Na meaningful Bible-based conversation,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.97,0:47:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,let alone make return visits \Nand conduct Bible studies with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.60,0:47:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,After returning home \Nfrom preaching at night,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.24,0:47:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I would ask myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.17,0:47:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Did I have a meaningful share \Nin the ministry today?’
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.64,0:47:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a small rural town.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.65,0:47:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So many people are concerned \Nabout what their neighbors
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.98,0:47:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,would think if they talked with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.89,0:47:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So even those who were interested \Nin learning more about the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.99,0:47:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,were reluctant to have \NBible discussions with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.83,0:47:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It was really unfortunate.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.26,0:47:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We tried to figure out \Nthe right time to call on people,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.13,0:47:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and we found out \Nthat many householders are more relaxed
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.37,0:47:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and willing to talk about the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.81,0:47:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,if we visit them \Naround nine or ten o’clock in the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.21,0:47:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave much thought \Non how I could help my Bible students
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.72,0:47:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,have a regular intake of spiritual food.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.62,0:47:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,One of my students \Nworked from 9 a.m. to 10 p.m.,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.42,0:47:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,so I asked her if we could arrange
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.03,0:48:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to study early in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.03,0:48:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.03,0:48:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I often tell my Bible students,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.16,0:48:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Just call me whenever you have \Na little time to talk.’
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.87,0:48:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,When I get those calls, \Nno matter what time it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.54,0:48:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s time to rush out that door.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.18,0:48:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There was one elderly lady \Nwho was in her early 80’s
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.65,0:48:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,who had attended church all her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.15,0:48:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,To accommodate her needs,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.19,0:48:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I visited her \Naround nine or ten o’clock in the evening
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.32,0:48:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,for our Bible studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.60,0:48:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I would come home \Nfeeling tired and hungry,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.30,0:48:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but the satisfaction of knowing
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.47,0:48:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that I’ve helped her learn \Nmore about the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.90,0:48:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,enables me to maintain my joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.11,0:48:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I am able to conduct \Nabout 12 Bible studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.64,0:48:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I try to “become all things \Nto people of all sorts”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.22,0:48:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to look after their needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.92,0:49:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And it brings me great satisfaction and joy
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.32,0:49:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to see my studies make progress
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.32,0:49:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because that’s really how Jehovah wants us
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.32,0:49:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to be carrying out our ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.83,0:49:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You might feel that you’ve worked \Nevery corner of your home territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.07,0:49:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But just like a literal fisherman \Nadapts to the time when the fish are biting,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.97,0:49:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to work when people can be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.31,0:49:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Cast your nets into productive waters!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.21,0:49:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Our sister arranged her schedule \Nto call on her Bible student
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.55,0:49:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,at nine or ten in the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.19,0:49:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we want to use good judgment
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.42,0:49:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to call at times that are both practical \Nand safe for our territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.19,0:49:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But by being adaptable in when, where,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.30,0:49:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,or how we preach the good news,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.73,0:49:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we may yield good results like those \Nof our fellow Witnesses in South Korea.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.14,0:49:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This will help us to have \Na meaningful share in the all-important work
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.68,0:50:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of finding those who \Nare “rightly disposed for everlasting life.”
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.28,0:50:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Regular pioneers work in a powerful way
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.49,0:50:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to help their brothers and sisters \Nget the most out of their ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.99,0:50:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But does that mean \Nthat they’re impervious to being in a rut,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.00,0:50:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,as mentioned earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.03,0:50:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following dramatization,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.43,0:50:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,see how one pioneer sister comes to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.84,0:50:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the need to adjust her approach \Nto the field ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.69,0:50:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It was really nice of Maria \Nto invite me in service.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.10,0:50:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But I already have plans with Sarah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.31,0:51:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We have similar service schedules,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.48,0:51:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and we really enjoy working together.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.39,0:51:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I try to get most of my time \Nduring the week, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.06,0:51:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone made plans to work together?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.03,0:51:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . though I do meet with the group \Nsometimes on Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.73,0:51:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Martin, \Ncan you work with Rachel today?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.84,0:51:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.34,0:51:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone made plans to work together?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.88,0:51:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. \NJoanna, you can work with Sarah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.86,0:51:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone made plans to work together?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.86,0:51:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sarah, do you want to go with me \Nto a Bible study?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.09,0:51:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Could I work with Alisha?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.03,0:51:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.39,0:51:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, let’s work together.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.73,0:51:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Joanna, could you two work together, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.43,0:51:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, I’d love to.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.87,0:52:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But I’ve just arranged to work with Sarah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.87,0:52:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.90,0:52:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh. \NNo problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.24,0:52:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria, could you work with this sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.06,0:52:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,While doing my Bible reading that night,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.93,0:52:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really affected
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.80,0:52:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,by the words found \Nat 2 Corinthians 6:12, 13:
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.44,0:52:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“You are restricted \Nin your own tender affections . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.71,0:52:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Open your hearts wide.”
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.28,0:52:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It struck me that some in the congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.89,0:52:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,missed out on a beautiful blessing
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.56,0:52:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,by drawing away from the apostle Paul.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.93,0:53:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized I was limiting my joy as well
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.63,0:53:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,by not working with more in the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.00,0:53:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going through the motions \Nof pioneering,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.31,0:53:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but I was stuck in the same routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.51,0:53:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you, Maria?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.31,0:53:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. And you?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.91,0:53:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me ask you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.91,0:53:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you join me on a Bible study Saturday?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.02,0:53:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I’d love that! Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.12,0:53:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s great.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.92,0:53:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So later we’ll make the arrangements. OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.65,0:53:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The meeting is starting.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.99,0:53:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We’d like to invite everyone \Nto take your seats
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.49,0:53:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,because our meeting is about to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.86,0:53:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,My student liked Maria and Isabelle so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.70,0:53:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I really learned a lot from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.31,0:53:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I started going out regularly \Non the weekends . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.32,0:53:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone made plans to work together?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.88,0:54:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . and working with different ones \Nin the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.06,0:54:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And I learned more about Sister Martin
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.83,0:54:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,after one day in the ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.30,0:54:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,than I had in years \Nof seeing her at meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.00,0:54:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sarah and I still enjoy working together.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.00,0:54:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But I’ve found that by working \Nwith a variety of friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.57,0:54:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,my own joy has increased.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.06,0:54:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m so glad I ‘opened my heart wide.’
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.37,0:54:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Joanna came to realize \Nthat her privilege of full-time service
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.37,0:54:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,was more than just hours and a schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.68,0:54:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,By working with a variety \Nof sisters in the ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.01,0:55:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and supporting her field service group,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.48,0:55:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,she could strengthen and encourage others.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.88,0:55:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It was within her power to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.49,0:55:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But with what result?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.62,0:55:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It rejuvenated her ministry!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.59,0:55:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We truly appreciate \Nthe love and sacrifice of our pioneers.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.57,0:55:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you been inspired \Nto make a change in your ministry?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.74,0:55:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether big or small, \Nat home or abroad,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.57,0:55:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we can find the satisfaction that comes
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.24,0:55:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,from reinvigorating our ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.18,0:55:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the theme featured \Nin the music video entitled
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.55,0:55:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m Making a Change.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.66,0:55:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Been thinking it over—\NEach day it seems
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.20,0:56:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,My serving Jehovah \NFalls into the same routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.11,0:56:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The things that I’m doing now \NI’ve always done.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.41,0:56:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s clear that I need to break out—\NOut of my comfort zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.05,0:56:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I’m making a change starting from today. \NI’m turning a page, yes, I’m on my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.73,0:56:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, I see what I need to do. \NI’m changing direction and trusting in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.49,0:56:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s gonna take courage, \NBut now I see
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.19,0:57:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How changing my thinking \NRenews and refreshes me.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.10,0:57:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m trying some new things, \Nand I’m energized.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.67,0:57:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There were doors that were opening wide, \NBut I never realized.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.65,0:57:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So I’m making a change, and I’m on my way. \NI’m turning a page each and ev’ry day.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.79,0:57:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, I see what I need to do. \NI’m changing direction and trusting in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.68,0:57:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then, I remember when \NIt seemed it wouldn’t happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.99,0:58:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Some days, well, I have to say, \NI didn’t know why.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.69,0:58:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But now I can see just how \NMy boldness led to blessings.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.30,0:58:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure there’ll be many more \NAs time goes rolling by.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.88,0:58:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I’m turning a page each and ev’ry day. \NI’m making some changes along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.98,0:58:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, I saw what I had to do, \NAnd you gave me your blessing
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.42,0:58:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,for trusting in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.63,0:58:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So I’m making a change starting from today. \NI’m turning a page, yes, I’m on my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.67,0:58:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, I see what I need to do. \NI’m changing direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.95,0:59:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So I’m making a change, and I’m on my way. \NI’m turning a page each and ev’ry day.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.62,0:59:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, I see what I need to do. \NI’m changing direction
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.00,0:59:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and trusting in you—
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.00,0:59:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Trusting in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.90,0:59:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governing Body deeply appreciates \Nthe work of each Kingdom publisher.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.90,0:59:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You dear brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.14,0:59:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,are having a regular share \Nin the preaching work,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.01,0:59:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and we commend you for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.51,1:00:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be sure \Nthat “God is not unrighteous
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.45,1:00:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to forget your work \Nand the love you showed for his name,”
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.12,1:00:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,as the Bible says at Hebrews 6:10.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.82,1:00:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Just knowing that can help us \Nto take a fresh look at our ministry
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.83,1:00:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and can invigorate us \Nto participate to the fullest extent.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.60,1:00:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,To conclude,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.93,1:00:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,we bring you greetings
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.94,1:00:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,from Bosnia and Herzegovina.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.21,1:00:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This mountainous region has a rich history
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.08,1:00:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,as a traditional meeting place
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.21,1:00:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,between eastern and western cultures;
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.71,1:00:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it dates from the Middle Ages.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.55,1:00:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the diverse religious beliefs \Nwithin the country,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.19,1:00:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the 1,160 publishers
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.42,1:00:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,must adapt their preaching methods
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.49,1:00:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to appeal to the hearts of those who listen.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.40,1:00:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the city of Mostar,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.66,1:00:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,which sits on the Neretva River.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.23,1:00:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The Neretva River
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.94,1:00:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,flows for nearly 230 kilometers,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.84,1:01:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,or almost 143 miles.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.28,1:01:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Mostar was a former front line \Nduring the wars of the 1990’s,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.11,1:01:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and many buildings still bear the marks
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.48,1:01:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of the intense fighting that took place.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.92,1:01:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, the aftermath \Nleft many people in this region
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.09,1:01:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with emotional and mental scars.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.89,1:01:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters are working hard
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.83,1:01:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring the hope of something good
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.90,1:01:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to those in need.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.17,1:01:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In the 1930’s, \Na pioneer brother named Alfred Tuček
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.07,1:01:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,spearheaded the preaching work \Nin the city of Mostar.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.21,1:01:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He was actually one of the first \Nin the former Yugoslavia to pioneer.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.88,1:01:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, the congregation in Mostar \Nhas about 60 publishers,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.02,1:01:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,including nine pioneers \Nand four field missionaries.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.42,1:01:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They bring their warm love and greetings
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.43,1:01:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to all of us around the world!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.33,1:01:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.90,1:02:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,from the world headquarters \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses.
